page.title: 09MRS LOCK'S INTERVIEW
page.content: LOCAL HISTORY PEOPLE HOUSING Mrs Lock opened the door and showed us in.And we sat down.She introduced us to her husband.We asked the questions and she answered them. Mrs Lock lives in Andrews Cottage in Bentworth,which is detached.She has lived there 8 years.The people who lived there before was Mr & Mrs Sylens & Mr & Mrs Hallally. She lives in a brick house with a tile roof.She has a garden and she likes the garden. She likes Bentworth but she does not like the wind. She has 4 Wippets. by Terri & Joanne
